 Children 2011.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; font-style:italic">Out from the Shadows:  Sexual Violence Against Children with Disabilities.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt"> Joint </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt">Communique</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt"> 13 November 2013.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; font-style:italic">Keeping her Safe:  Protecting Girls and Women in Emergencies.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn10"></a><a href="#_ftnref10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt"> See point 30 in DFID September 2011.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; font-style:italic">The UK Government’s Humanitarian Policy.  </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/67468/The_20UK_20Government_s_20Humanitarian_20Policy_20-_20September_202011_20-_20Final.pdf"><span style="color:#0563c1; font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/67468/The_20UK_20Government_s_20Humanitarian_20Policy_20-_20September_202011_20-_20Final.pdf</span></a><span style="color:#0563c1; font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn11"></a><a href="#_ftnref11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt">World Health Organizaton, 2008. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; font-style:italic">Preventing violence and reducing its impact: how development agencies can help</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn12"></a><a href="#_ftnref12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt"> See Handicap Internation